The term '''''telematics''''' is used in a number of ways:
*The [[integrated]] use of [[telecommunication]]s and [[informatics]], also known as ICT ([[Information and Communications Technology]]). More specifically it is the science of sending, receiving and storing information via telecommunication devices.
*More narrowly and commonly, telematics is applied specifically to the use of [[Global Positioning System]] technology integrated with computers and mobile communications technology.
*Most narrowly, the term is used to refer to the use of such systems within [[road vehicle]]s, in which case the term '''vehicle telematics''' may be used.